      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GREAT PROMISE (4) his hard to knock on her recent efforts, leading last start as the the race favourite and being gunned down by a smart one. Her form stacks right up for this event though and back to 1100m is no issue. Can go one better this time around. ARTIE'S STORM (7) comes across from Victoria and should be better for a recent trial at Belmont. The blinkers go on for the first time and the form she brings across from the east is solid. Creates plenty of interest. FLASH DANCER (2) led last start and was solid from the front over 1200m at Belmont in a stronger race. He drops back in grade now and Chris Parnham now hops on board. Ready to peak now third-up and he can get back to winning ways. BELAURA STAR (1) comes here off an 81-day break and was sound at 1300m here before the break. Can be in the finish again. FLYING FRANKIE (3) won't be far away first-up.",
